metadata.name: NYC
metadata.description:
I’m a first-generation American. My parents emigrated from quiet villages in Ireland and Italy to Ellis Island in the 1950s, to discover upon arrival of the sensory overload of New York City.

“NYC” — the first destination this Roam collection — captures that cacophony and my love of the city. 

Collectors, thank you for considering this collage that promises legacy — NYC will never go dark.
